At Stake in this Election: 




The Presidency of Iceland 




Government Structure:  




Chief of State: President Guðni Thorlacius JÓHANNESON (since 1 August 2016) 






Head of Government: Prime Minister Bjarni BENEDIKTSSON (since 9 April 2024) 






Assembly: unicameral Parliament (Alþingi) with 63 seats 




Electoral System:  




The President is directly elected by simple majority vote and may serve unlimited 4-year terms. 






The parliamentary majority leader is appointed Prime Minister following legislative elections. 






 In Parliament, all 63 members are directly elected via closed-list proportional representation vote. All members serve 4-year terms, and there are no term limits. 




Last Election: 


In the 2020 presidential election, Guðni JÓHANNESON won with 92.2% of the vote, defeating Sturla JÓNSSON. Voter turnout was 66.93%. 


Information for Voters: 


Fyrir kjósendur / For voters (in Icelandic and English) 


Key Deadlines: 






Candidate filing deadline: 26 April 2024 






Voter registration deadline: N/A; voter registration is passive and the voter roll is updated by 24 April 2024.
